<para>
  <classname>GlobalErrorScaling</classname> scales the error estimate
  for each &field; component <inlineequation><alt
  role="tex">\(\phi\)</alt></inlineequation> at each &node; by
  <equation>
    <alt role="tex">
      \[ \Delta t \left|\frac{d\phi}{dt}\right| \]
    </alt>
  </equation>
  and then returns the maximum value.  This is supposed to control the
  cumulative error over the entire time evolution.
</para>

